Requirements:
Name
Description
Stakeholder_Requirement-1
The biosensor system will measure toxin levels in food samples.
Stakeholder_Requirement-2
The biosensor system will show the sensor signal during the assay.
Stakeholder_Requirement-3
The biosensor system will show the result (if the sample has toxin or not) at the end of the assay.
Stakeholder_Requirement-4
The biosensor system will prevent any contamination between samples to be measured.
Stakeholder_Requirement-5
The biosensor system will not cause harm to the user by releasing contaminated samples.
Stakeholder_Requirement-6
 
Technical_Requirement-1
With the command of the device operator:
   The biosensor system will desorb the microfluidics in order to prevent the microbial growth of the tubing.
Technical_Requirement-2
With the command of the device operator:
   The biosensor system will prime the microfluidics in order to change the buffer solution in the tubing.
Technical_Requirement-3
With the command of the device operator:
   The biosensor system will perform a quality control procedure to the biochip that will be used for the assay.
Technical_Requirement-4
Device operator plans the assay protocol, then:
   The biosensor system will allow the operator to set the assay protocol including the position of the reagents tubes, reagents flow rates, duration of the fluid flow and duration of the signal.
Technical_Requirement-5
With the command of the device operator:
   The biosensor system will run the assay protocol defined by the device operator.
Technical_Requirement-6
With the command of the device operator:
   The biosensor system will run the assay protocol defined by the device operator.
Technical_Requirement-7
With the command of the device operator:
   The biosensor system will show the signals real-time during the assay run.
Technical_Requirement-8
With the command of the device operator:
   The biosensor system will save the assay signal results.
